						<td class="justify">
							<p><strong>Middleware</strong> has emerged as a critical 
								second level of the enterprise IT infrastructure. 
								Even though this software is not visible to users, 
								it enables sharing resources and system interoperabilty 
								across a distributed system despite differences in 
								OS platforms and networks. A middleware is a software 
								layer that sits between the network/OSs and the applications. 
								Examples include <em>DCE</em>, <em>CORBA</em>, <em>DCOM</em>, 
								<em>MoM</em>, and Microsofts <em>.NET</em> technology. 
								Middleware provides location transparencies and services 
								such as communication, identification, authentication, 
								authorization, directories, and security.</p>
							<p>The primary goal of <strong>MIDLAB</strong> is to support 
								leading-edge research and development on middleware 
								bridging the gap between the latest research results 
								and the current technologies. In particular main MIDLAB 
								targets are the <em>study, the design and analysis 
								of novel middleware platforms able to increase the 
								QoS in a raw client/server interaction with respect 
								to reliability, consistency and predictability</em>. 
								This is done through the design and the development 
								of innovative prototypes, the presence in leading-edge 
								projects, research on fundamental aspects of distributed 
								computing and the testing of middleware plaftforms 
								present on the market.</p>
							<p>MIDLAB currently is involved in the following projects: 
								<a href="http://www.newcastle.research.ec.org/midas/index.html" target="_blank">MIDAS</a>, 
								<a href="http://www.eu-publi.com/" target="_blank">EU-Publi.com</a>, 
								<a href="http://www.dis.uniroma1.it/%7Edq" target="_blank">DaQuincis</a>, 
								<a href="http://black.elet.polimi.it/mais/" target="_blank">MAIS</a>, 
								<a href="http://zeus.elet.polimi.it/is-manet/" target="_blank">IS-MANET</a>.</p>

							<table border="0" align="center" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="10">
								<tr>
									<td align="right"><a href="http://www.minema.di.fc.ul.pt/index.html" target="_blank"><img src="images/minema.gif" border="0"></a></td>
									<td class="justify">
										<p>MIDLAB is a member of MiNEMA.</p>
										<p>MiNEMA is an European Science Foundation (ESF)  Scientific Programme aiming to bring together European groups from  different communities working on  middleware for mobile environment. The  programme intends to foster the  definition and implementation of  widely recognized middleware  abstractions for new and emerging  mobile applications.</p>
